        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName> <date>7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Shebat 5611</date></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>6 Great alie<add>&#63;</add> St. Goodmans fields</placeName></p>
			<p>My Dear Revd. Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Notwithstanding the shortness of the days&#44; as<lb/> well as the pressure of business&#44; in order not to <sic>loose</sic> a moment or allow<lb/> a port to pass I devoted myself at once to write a long letter to <persName>Mr. A. Hart</persName><lb/> on <date>Friday</date> last and flatter myself that I have done it <add>Hebrew</add> and<lb/> most powerful&#44; that it was impossible I could have ventured to have done it<lb/> equally for a dearest brother&#59; I hope it will have a good effect&#44; there<lb/> was also one enclosed for you which no doubt you have received from him<lb/> in hopes that you will give a little hearing to my counsel though<lb/> your superior talents do not require it&#44; but Dr. friend <hi rend="underline">give in a little</hi><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>. Allow me my dr. brother <hi rend="underline">most particularly</hi> to solicit you that whatever<lb/> I might have said to you concerning the young man &#38; &#40;though nothing against<lb/> him&#41; be in the greatest <hi rend="underline">confidence</hi> &#38; secrecy <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; for your experience<lb/> has taught you that from one word where there are party feelings&#44; how<lb/> a <sic>mans</sic> name is handled about and what confessions &#38;c he may be<lb/> placed in&#44; therefore I entirely <hi rend="underline">rely</hi> and <hi rend="underline">depend</hi> on your <hi rend="underline">honor</hi> that not<lb/> <sic>an</sic> hint come out of your mouth. He is quite astonished at his not having<lb/> received any answer. I shall be most thankful to you to let me know<lb/> at once state of affairs and <sic>moreso</sic> concerning my letter of which I have<lb/> no doubt <persName>Mr. Hart</persName> will communicate with you in hopes <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> when I said to you in my last &#8220;he was <hi rend="underline">sly</hi> in this affair for he is in friendly<lb/> terms <del>to same</del> with me &#38; ought in every respects have communicated what<lb/> he was going to do for many motives&#8212;I now write on a different subject<lb/> of much less importance for which cause I did not wish nor had the time</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>to communicate to you. I have no doubt you have read in the Jewish<lb/> Chronicle <date>25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Oct.</date> my Discourse <hi rend="underline">Divine Judgements improved</hi>. Thousands<lb/> are the private motives for my having published it <add>Hebrew</add> but will<lb/> communicate it to you when all affairs settled <add>Hebrew</add> I have printed them<lb/> <hi rend="underline">neatly</hi> with my chief object the long Dedication to our Gent<hi rend="sup">n</hi> Elders&#44; as<lb/> well as the letter of the Archbishop of <placeName>Canterbury</placeName> to me&#44; they are in a<lb/> small size about 16 pages with wrappers&#44; <del>the object is</del> my object<lb/> is not for money for the publication would you be pleased to let me know<lb/> if a number of them could be sold there&#8212;how many copies&#63; to whom<lb/> shall I send them&#63; whether you would take the trouble and the <hi rend="underline">minimum</hi><lb/> price such pamphlets are sold at your place I should with much<lb/> pleasure send you some&#44; it is most horrible &#38; distressing to see how the<lb/> productions are treated here&#44; I have distributed a great number among<lb/> our own nation &#40;with my respects&#41; not even &#8220;<hi rend="underline">thank you</hi>&#8221; was its value&#44; so is<lb/> the state of literary productions <persName>Sir Moses</persName> the only one who <sic>realy</sic> on all<lb/> occasions he is the man. I trust I shall soon have a good long letter<lb/> from you with good tidings <add>Hebrew</add> wishing you again every prosperity</p>
          <p rend="indent(\8)">I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Dear &#38; Revd Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">yours very truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">David Meldola</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">P&#58;S&#58; you will be pleased to forward</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">the enclosed as soon as possible to <persName>Mr. A. Hart.</persName></p>
          
        </body>
